00:18:15,225 --> 00:18:16,576
Is there something wrong?

280
00:18:16,819 --> 00:18:17,850
Well..no

281
00:18:18,850 --> 00:18:20,537
I was surprised to hear that out of the blue.

282
00:18:22,380 --> 00:18:25,896
I want you to do an export job when you return

283
00:18:26,420 --> 00:18:27,381
Thank you

284
00:18:28,787 --> 00:18:30,170
How old are you now?

285
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,076
I'm 32

286
00:18:33,194 --> 00:18:38,061
Managing Director Domoto studied abroad when he was 35 and I was 37.

287
00:18:39,615 --> 00:18:40,623
You are lucky

288
00:18:41,405 --> 00:18:44,295
You are one of the best executive candidates

289
00:18:45,123 --> 00:18:45,842
Good luck

290
00:18:47,748 --> 00:18:48,662
Thank you very much

291
00:18:49,428 --> 00:18:52,170
That's very sudden.

292
00:18:53,303 --> 00:18:58,022
If you leave in the middle of next month, you only have about 20 days left.

293
00:18:58,350 --> 00:18:58,920
Yeah

294
00:19:00,233 --> 00:19:01,881
So please meet me

295
00:19:03,334 --> 00:19:05,069
yeah, when?

296
00:19:05,467 --> 00:19:06,389
Tomorrow, Sunday

297
00:19:07,162 --> 00:19:09,303
Then I'll be waiting at the usual place

298
00:19:10,006 --> 00:19:11,709
No, I'll visit your home

299
00:19:12,209 --> 00:19:12,662
What?

300
00:19:13,545 --> 00:19:14,467
I'm not comfortable outside

301
00:19:14,928 --> 00:19:15,756
But...

302
00:19:15,865 --> 00:19:16,483
IS that bad?

303
00:19:57,217 --> 00:19:58,389
What's wrong with you?

304
00:19:59,084 --> 00:20:00,030
Come in

305
00:20:05,522 --> 00:20:08,662
Are you interested in where I live?

306
00:20:10,647 --> 00:20:11,998
I don't mean that

307
00:20:12,194 --> 00:20:16,217
You want to know who I am,right?

308
00:20:25,483 --> 00:20:27,045
How many years are you going to Europe?

309
00:20:28,842 --> 00:20:29,451
About a year

310
00:20:32,162 --> 00:20:32,819
That's so long

311
00:20:35,084 --> 00:20:38,444
I'll be lonely without you

312
00:20:41,803 --> 00:20:43,912
I go to the shooting range alone again

313
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:52,889
I had a strange relationship with you

314
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:59,725
I don't want to leave you without knowing anything about you.

315
00:21:02,647 --> 00:21:06,467
When you found out we were splitting up, you became very bossy.

316
00:21:16,381 --> 00:21:17,451
I love you

317
00:21:28,451 --> 00:21:29,155
What?

318
00:21:31,295 --> 00:21:33,662
You know why I'm here?

319
00:21:36,530 --> 00:21:37,959
I found this place to be the safest.

320
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:44,264
If you meet with me, no one will come to see you today.

321
00:21:44,350 --> 00:21:46,740
Don't say that, please.

322
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:52,780
From the beginning you didn't think I was a normal female, right?

323
00:22:55,162 --> 00:22:55,803
But...

324
00:22:56,287 --> 00:22:59,342
Didn't you think I'm Kasumi-san's woman?

325
00:23:06,263 --> 00:23:06,911
Are you scared?

326
00:23:08,227 --> 00:23:12,592
He is very powerful

327
00:23:15,146 --> 00:23:16,520
He's easy to fire me

328
00:23:20,482 --> 00:23:21,740
You'll leave from me?

329
00:23:28,271 --> 00:23:28,849
I'll take you away from him.

330
00:23:55,115 --> 00:23:55,716
Good morning

331
00:23:57,310 --> 00:23:58,654
I'm sorry

332
00:24:07,740 --> 00:24:09,834
You don't seem to look at the newspaper

333
00:24:10,834 --> 00:24:12,341
Ms. Akatsuka was killed

334
00:24:13,693 --> 00:24:14,177
What?

335
00:24:16,162 --> 00:24:16,771
Good morning

336
00:24:23,959 --> 00:24:24,974
Was she killed by a robbery?

337
00:24:25,388 --> 00:24:27,904
There was no mention of it in the papers.

338
00:24:29,005 --> 00:24:30,091
I'm sorry

339
00:24:30,466 --> 00:24:32,505
For you and for her

340
00:24:32,724 --> 00:24:34,396
I had nothing to do with it.

341
00:24:35,209 --> 00:24:35,873
You sure?

342
00:24:36,771 --> 00:24:39,248
It can be dangerous to have a woman alone

343
00:24:39,974 --> 00:24:41,216
You had better get married early

344
00:24:41,709 --> 00:24:43,115
With the father of the child on your stomach

345
00:24:43,943 --> 00:24:44,599
Fuji-san

346
00:24:46,037 --> 00:24:47,966
The truth is, I'm not pregnant.

347
00:24:48,732 --> 00:24:49,466
Good morning

348
00:24:55,419 --> 00:24:57,364
I didn't do it because Akatsuka-san taught me to lie.

349
00:24:58,075 --> 00:24:59,013
She taught you?

350
00:24:59,802 --> 00:25:00,404
Yes

351
00:25:01,810 --> 00:25:06,654
I got angry when I heard from Mr. Furuya about your relationship with Ms.Akatsuka

352
00:25:07,552 --> 00:25:12,709
I told her about a company trip with you in addition to the results of the pregnancy test

353
00:25:14,044 --> 00:25:17,216
I thought it would be good for her to get away from you.

354
00:25:17,802 --> 00:25:19,826
I'm sorry but I didn't love her

355
00:25:20,240 --> 00:25:22,834
Oh she said same

356
00:25:24,748 --> 00:25:27,654
So she told me to lie that I was pregnant

357
00:25:28,294 --> 00:25:30,560
I thought you might be willing to get married

358
00:25:31,794 --> 00:25:33,709
I thought I could get a reward from you even if it didn't work

359
00:25:36,459 --> 00:25:38,373
You look very troubled.

360
00:25:40,294 --> 00:25:44,567
I think the police will investigate the person related to her

361
00:25:46,411 --> 00:25:48,654
But don't worry,
I won't talk anything

362
00:25:49,709 --> 00:25:52,310
I decided to quit the company and get married this month

363
00:26:04,537 --> 00:26:05,537
Good morning

364
00:26:08,779 --> 00:26:11,294
It seems that Dr. Akatsuka was killed.

365
00:26:14,591 --> 00:26:16,177
Hey, cheer up

366
00:26:19,646 --> 00:26:23,959
I don't know what you think but
She is not the subject of your marriage

367
00:26:26,982 --> 00:26:30,279
You suspected that I and she had a relationship

368
00:26:30,904 --> 00:26:33,552
I went to her hospital to get money from her

369
00:26:34,365 --> 00:26:34,888
Money?

370
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:36,248
Of course there was interest

371
00:26:37,544 --> 00:26:38,146
Damn it

372
00:26:39,216 --> 00:26:41,169
The loan book I wrote the other day should be at her place

373
00:26:42,279 --> 00:26:43,834
That's inconvenient

374
00:26:46,912 --> 00:26:48,443
Let me see the news paper

375
00:27:12,529 --> 00:27:18,849
No matter where you are last night, it has nothing to do with the murder

376
00:27:20,685 --> 00:27:21,412
I don't think so.

377
00:27:22,826 --> 00:27:24,779
I have a loan book I wrote in her house

378
00:27:26,162 --> 00:27:26,927
loan book?

379
00:27:28,138 --> 00:27:31,904
Actually, I borrowed 20,000 yen from her a week ago

380
00:27:33,482 --> 00:27:37,591
If the police find it, the police will look into my alibi

381
00:27:39,669 --> 00:27:43,060
But what time was that person killed yesterday?

382
00:27:44,021 --> 00:27:46,599
It seems to be around 3 pm

383
00:27:48,380 --> 00:27:49,412
3 pm?

384
00:27:53,919 --> 00:27:55,388
So What will you do?

385
00:27:57,255 --> 00:28:00,880
I can't tell anyone I've met you.
No one know that

386
00:28:02,951 --> 00:28:06,248
Only you can prove my alibi

387
00:28:13,599 --> 00:28:16,357
Just in case, If they find out about my relationship with Himako...

388
00:28:17,396 --> 00:28:19,216
Mr.Kasumi will get angry

389
00:28:20,294 --> 00:28:22,396
I may get rid of the company

390
00:28:23,536 --> 00:28:25,247
I need alibi

391
00:28:26,404 --> 00:28:27,998
Thinking too much makes my head hurt

392
00:28:28,974 --> 00:28:31,138
I need a natural alibi

393
00:28:32,482 --> 00:28:33,044
Oh yeah!

394
00:28:49,248 --> 00:28:52,560
It's unusual for him to come to the bar alone and drink so much

395
00:28:54,060 --> 00:28:56,709
He's a little crazy today

396
00:28:57,396 --> 00:28:59,373
He also has that kind of thing

397
00:28:59,779 --> 00:29:01,466
Oh welcome

398
00:29:01,802 --> 00:29:03,130
Let's drink again

399
00:29:04,740 --> 00:29:06,802
Your executive...

400
00:29:08,021 --> 00:29:09,162
That dirty man

401
00:29:09,216 --> 00:29:10,365
Mr.Domoto?

402
00:29:11,709 --> 00:29:13,732
I'll toast for him

403
00:29:14,044 --> 00:29:16,701
I'll toast for Yuzaki department chief

404
00:29:17,052 --> 00:29:17,880
Cheers!

405
00:29:21,052 --> 00:29:22,310
let's toast for Oike department chief

406
00:29:22,591 --> 00:29:25,201
He works so hard,
Cheers!

407
00:29:27,380 --> 00:29:29,771
I'll toast for Miyama department chief

408
00:29:30,490 --> 00:29:32,489
Miyama?
I hate him

409
00:29:33,318 --> 00:29:34,193
What's wrong?

410
00:29:36,185 --> 00:29:37,662
It's non of your business

411
00:29:38,044 --> 00:29:40,255
I'll toast for Fuji chief

412
00:29:41,763 --> 00:29:43,833
You are so nice today

413
00:29:43,858 --> 00:29:46,068
You seem to have an ulterior motive.

414
00:29:46,341 --> 00:29:48,099
It's up to you

415
00:29:48,201 --> 00:29:50,091
Because you are still single

416
00:30:01,224 --> 00:30:01,990
What time is it?

417
00:30:02,709 --> 00:30:04,091
It's 10 am

418
00:30:04,388 --> 00:30:06,685
I had seven years of no tardiness, no absenteeism, and it was for nothing.

419
00:30:07,474 --> 00:30:08,912
Because you drunk so much

420
00:30:09,747 --> 00:30:11,716
I also have a hangover

421
00:30:15,755 --> 00:30:18,857
Did you have anything with Mr. Miyama?

422
00:30:20,193 --> 00:30:21,974
Well...nothing

423
00:30:24,537 --> 00:30:25,193
Why you ask me?

424
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:30,404
You were in a bad mood when you talked about him yesterday

425
00:30:33,872 --> 00:30:34,701
I was?

426
00:30:36,654 --> 00:30:38,857
I'm drunk so I don't remember anything

427
00:30:49,951 --> 00:30:50,513
You OK?

428
00:30:53,451 --> 00:30:54,435
I'll take this

429
00:31:05,997 --> 00:31:07,162
Are you Satoru Fuji?

430
00:31:07,771 --> 00:31:08,044
Yes

431
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:12,474
We are the police.
We would like to talk to you about Ms. Akatsuka's case.

432
00:31:13,833 --> 00:31:14,201
OK

433
00:31:19,966 --> 00:31:22,349
You mean that loan book?

434
00:31:23,568 --> 00:31:26,099
I suddenly needed money for a private matter

435
00:31:26,997 --> 00:31:29,771
You are the chief of a large company, right?

436
00:31:30,318 --> 00:31:32,060
You are single, right?

437
00:31:32,466 --> 00:31:34,232
I don't save money

438
00:31:34,943 --> 00:31:37,771
Our salary is not as good as you think

439
00:31:39,341 --> 00:31:42,810
If I have a special relationship with her, I won't write a loan book

440
00:31:43,458 --> 00:31:44,162
I see

441
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:49,888
By the way,Where were you between 2 pm and 4 pm when the incident happened?

442
00:31:51,427 --> 00:31:53,310
That's a very unpleasant question for me

443
00:31:53,622 --> 00:31:54,583
I'm sorry

444
00:31:54,787 --> 00:31:56,990
Because this is my job

445
00:31:57,708 --> 00:32:01,646
Ask as many people as I can, the more chances I have of finding a clue.

446
00:32:01,747 --> 00:32:02,544
Please understand us

447
00:32:03,060 --> 00:32:05,646
I was watching a movie at the cinema that time

448
00:32:06,154 --> 00:32:06,919
Ar star cinema?

449
00:32:07,552 --> 00:32:08,052
Yes

450
00:32:08,435 --> 00:32:12,005
Did you meet someone in the cinema?

451
00:32:13,630 --> 00:32:16,755
Well...there was nothing.

452
00:32:17,779 --> 00:32:22,060
And I heard that there is a person in your company who has a special relationship with her.

453
00:32:22,966 --> 00:32:24,364
I have no idea

454
00:32:24,404 --> 00:32:28,380
We just refer to it.
I'll keep what you say secret

455
00:32:29,474 --> 00:32:33,419
My colleague Furuya said he wanted to marry her

456
00:32:33,630 --> 00:32:34,794
Mr.Furuya

457
00:32:35,044 --> 00:32:35,568
And?

458
00:32:36,372 --> 00:32:39,841
He sometimes went to her clinic

459
00:32:45,505 --> 00:32:48,802
Please make a copy of this minutes

460
00:32:48,827 --> 00:32:50,599
Ah, chief

461
00:32:50,927 --> 00:32:51,318
What?

462
00:32:51,591 --> 00:32:53,505
Is it true that Mr. Furuya was called by the police?

463
00:32:55,841 --> 00:32:58,997
Police are investigating who was in and out of her clinic

464
00:33:00,537 --> 00:33:01,701
They has asked me

465
00:33:02,630 --> 00:33:03,552
They has asked you?

466
00:33:03,577 --> 00:33:04,115
Yes

467
00:33:05,716 --> 00:33:09,169
The section chief is calling you

468
00:33:10,716 --> 00:33:11,443
Hello

469
00:33:14,333 --> 00:33:15,068
I get it

470
00:33:16,091 --> 00:33:16,857
I'll go there now

471
00:33:21,662 --> 00:33:22,693
Welcome

472
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:25,654
Hi

473
00:33:27,365 --> 00:33:28,138
How are you?

474
00:33:29,029 --> 00:33:30,708
I thought it was not good to talk at the company

475
00:33:31,513 --> 00:33:32,341
Is it because of the police?

476
00:33:34,044 --> 00:33:35,622
I felt very unpleasant

477
00:33:36,529 --> 00:33:38,349
The police are suspicious of you too

478
00:33:40,865 --> 00:33:44,630
Mr. Furuya also said he's going to marry Mr. Akatsuka, so he's quite suspected by the police.

479
00:33:45,052 --> 00:33:49,576
He had an alibi because he was hiking to the mountains that day with a colleague from the company

480
00:33:51,068 --> 00:33:54,287
By the way The police have asked me a lot about you

481
00:33:54,724 --> 00:33:56,287
You have an alibi, right?

482
00:33:56,880 --> 00:33:59,130
Yes I was watching a movie

483
00:34:00,216 --> 00:34:00,888
That's good

484
00:34:01,669 --> 00:34:03,286
I'm sorry to worry you

485
00:34:03,404 --> 00:34:07,263
Anyway, the police are very persistent when they suspect something.

486
00:34:08,583 --> 00:34:10,810
I think you should prove your innocence early

487
00:34:10,872 --> 00:34:11,427
I know

488
00:34:12,552 --> 00:34:14,201
Let me tell you something else.

489
00:34:15,076 --> 00:34:17,763
Did you hear anything from Director Yuzaki?

490
00:34:19,435 --> 00:34:19,802
Well

491
00:34:21,240 --> 00:34:23,935
I see.
You've been through a lot, haven't you?

492
00:34:25,083 --> 00:34:27,865
I think you don't have to worry because you have an alibi

493
00:34:29,005 --> 00:34:29,966
I was relieved to hear that

494
00:34:32,216 --> 00:34:34,638
By the way, about your study abroad in Europe

495
00:34:36,544 --> 00:34:38,701
That has been postponed

496
00:34:40,169 --> 00:34:44,888
The company wants to let you go after your innocence has been proven.

497
00:34:45,802 --> 00:34:48,177
So you need to wait

498
00:34:57,107 --> 00:35:01,771
Do the police trust what you said?

499
00:35:03,208 --> 00:35:04,396
I have no idea

500
00:35:05,849 --> 00:35:09,419
What if your alibi isn't recognized?

501
00:35:18,662 --> 00:35:22,396
Then I have no choice but to talk about you

502
00:35:22,630 --> 00:35:27,669
It's not good.
If you tell them that, we're over

503
00:35:30,185 --> 00:35:32,716
So What will you do?

504
00:35:34,599 --> 00:35:36,638
I have no choice but to find the culprit myself

505
00:35:39,576 --> 00:35:43,287
I absolutely have to find the culprit who is annoying us

506
00:35:44,529 --> 00:35:46,185
It's the only way to save me.

507
00:35:48,294 --> 00:35:50,880
I'm so scared

508
00:35:53,685 --> 00:35:55,396
Don't worry. you'll be fine

509
00:35:57,982 --> 00:35:59,521
I'll handle it.

510
00:36:02,302 --> 00:36:06,208
Oh..She was murdered, wasn't she?

511
00:36:07,075 --> 00:36:07,911
Is that true?

512
00:36:08,005 --> 00:36:08,576
Yes

513
00:36:09,279 --> 00:36:10,732
I'm sorry

514
00:36:10,779 --> 00:36:14,560
By the way, The man she brought with her, is he a regular here?

515
00:36:14,740 --> 00:36:16,317
He is not

516
00:36:16,435 --> 00:36:17,826
But you know about him,right?

517
00:36:18,779 --> 00:36:21,404
I can't talk about customer information

518
00:36:22,677 --> 00:36:24,740
This is for keeping quiet.

519
00:36:26,966 --> 00:36:28,763
I only know his name

520
00:36:29,287 --> 00:36:30,802
He is a person who speaks Osaka dialect called Mr. Sonoda.

521
00:36:30,827 --> 00:36:31,161
Osaka dialect?

522
00:36:31,224 --> 00:36:31,568
Yes

523
00:36:31,593 --> 00:36:32,544
What kind of work does he do?

524
00:36:32,654 --> 00:36:35,966
He said he was in the finance business in Hibiya.

525
00:36:48,005 --> 00:36:49,052
Thank you for waiting

526
00:36:53,951 --> 00:36:54,958
Who lives here now?

527
00:36:55,193 --> 00:36:56,154
teacher ’s aunt.

528
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:57,240
Is she a doctor after all?

529
00:36:57,520 --> 00:37:00,263
No,She is a Christian grandmother

530
00:37:01,076 --> 00:37:03,912
Can I work in your company's medical office?

531
00:37:04,240 --> 00:37:05,857
I am qualified as a nurse

532
00:37:06,091 --> 00:37:08,505
You had better ask Miyama than to me

533
00:37:08,849 --> 00:37:09,591
I don't like him

534
00:37:09,982 --> 00:37:10,607
Why?

535
00:37:10,841 --> 00:37:11,622
Well...

536
00:37:12,716 --> 00:37:14,919
Oh yeah,
I'd better to ask Yuzaki

537
00:37:15,271 --> 00:37:16,138
He ’s the director, right?

538
00:37:16,380 --> 00:37:17,755
Has he ever come?

539
00:37:17,919 --> 00:37:19,162
Yes 4,5 times before

540
00:37:22,646 --> 00:37:27,052
What kind of questions were you asked by the police?

541
00:37:27,365 --> 00:37:30,216
They asked who was often coming

542
00:37:31,029 --> 00:37:31,537
Then

543
00:37:32,669 --> 00:37:33,912
I told them all I knew

544
00:37:34,333 --> 00:37:37,490
Tokioka and Futuya from the Yachiyo company

545
00:37:37,779 --> 00:37:38,810
and you

546
00:37:38,835 --> 00:37:40,490
You told them about me

547
00:37:41,201 --> 00:37:42,818
Is Tokioka a person in the sales department?

548
00:37:45,138 --> 00:37:46,646
Did Miyama also come often?

549
00:37:47,404 --> 00:37:50,068
He was here a lot, but he was quiet.

550
00:37:52,130 --> 00:37:54,490
Do you know a man called Sonoda?

551
00:37:54,849 --> 00:37:55,599
Sonoda?

552
00:37:56,005 --> 00:37:57,521
He is a financial company who speaks Osaka dialect

553
00:37:57,919 --> 00:38:00,388
I don't know.
There was no such person in the patient

554
00:38:00,896 --> 00:38:01,747
Give me some water

